    <table border=0 cellpadding=3 cellspacing=0 bgcolor=cfcfbb width=100%><tr><td align=left>
    <font size=3 color="#363636"><b>Sleepers Tomb.. The essence of Balance in Everquest</b></font><br>
    <font size=2>
    Posted on Monday, February 12 @ 17:55:26 EST by <a href="http://www.noows.com">zamtil</a><font size=2>Contributed by: <a href="user.php?op=userinfo&uname=Xerexs">Xerexs</a></font></td></tr></table></td></tr></table><br><a href="search.php?query=&topic=30"><img src=images/topics/everquest.gif border=0 Alt="EverQuest" align=right hspace=10 vspace=10></a>When is enough.. enough?  Casters have seen there power dwindle and dwindle every day in the world of Everquest while melee classes consistently receive better weapons, haste items, right clickable items, proccing weapons, etc etc.   It used to be casters were needed because they either offered incredible DMG/TIME(short) ratio (Wizards) or incredible DMG/TIME(long) ratios (Necro/Wizards).  <br><br><br><br>However with the advent of velious uber hit point mobs / uber resist mobs high DMG/TIME(short) ratios are no longer needed hence making the wizard class effectively useless.  This is not even breaching the fact that Rogues almost outdamage wizards on the short time period even if the wizard is chain nuking.  This still leaves Necros/Magicians are potentially useful because of their staying damage power because of pets.  However because of the resists/level of the mobs most / all melee now outdamage a necro/magician over a 3 minute+ fight.  Rogues/Monks do upwards of 100 damage per second.  As a necromancer I can't do that much damage chain casting my best lifetap which by the way is resisted vs almost all encounters.
<br><br>
As bad as this is Verant continues to make it WORSE instead of better.  In sleepers tomb melee characters can look forward to obtaining 13/20 weapons +5 to all stats +5 to all resists 50hp 50 mana weapons that proc AVATAR.  What do casters have to look forward to?  How about <a href="http://www.noows.com/mig.php?currDir=./EverQuest/Fires%20of%20Heaven/Sleeper%27s%20Tomb&pageType=image&image=WritOfDragonkind.jpg"> Writ of Dragonkind.</a>Sorry but this item is far from the best primary item available already plus it in NO WAY makes a caster any more powerful.  How about <a href="http://www.noows.com/mig.php?currDir=./EverQuest/Fires%20of%20Heaven/Sleeper%27s%20Tomb&pageType=image&image=StaffOfTheMorningDew.jpg"> Staff of the Morning Dew.</a>  Uhhh.. this item doesnt come close to anything someone above level 45 would wear yet it drops from the same mobs that drop AVATAR proccing weapons.  The 4/12 ratio leaves this item promise however as Verant could easily attach a HIGH QUALITY proc such as Infusion, Lure of Ice, Clarity 3, Divine Light, etc etc to make this item something a caster would actually WANT.
<br><br>
My suggestion / solution to the ever widening span of balance is simple.  Add USEFUL procs/right click items with NON OBSCENE casting times to high level caster class items.  Wavecrasher for example would have been an excellent SHAMAN ONLY SPEAR.  The yawn could have stayed 70 percent maybe 50 percent.  This would let the best equipped shaman in essence MORE USEFUL then the Rune Etched wearing lvl 46 newbie.  Verant needs to ABANDON the static power caster concept in favor of an increasing power idea like melee currently enjoy.   If this is just too hard to do perhaps you could at least design level 60 loot to be better than sebilis drops.</td></tr></table><br></td><td>&nbsp;</td><td valign=top width=200>
