<br>
You kill Uber Mob X.  He normally drops that hoss elite caster cloak that is AC 14, INT +10, WIS +10, MANA +100.  Sure, that's nice, but it's not really making the caster any better, it increases the mana pool marginally and adds a tad of AC that isn't really going to help against Uber Mob X anyway.  What it really should be dropping is the "Cloak of Focusing", which would do something like a) increase damage output of all spells by 10%, b) decrease casting time on all spells by 10%, c) decrease mana cost by 10%, etc.  This would be a truly USEFUL item.  Warriors would keep getting their better weapons, and Wizards would keep getting items that increase the damage output on their spells (or modify other facets of spellcasting).  But like I said, it'd probably require extensive coding (total overhaul of the spell system perhaps).. not very likely, but it's something that should have been done from the beginning.<br>
<br>
